parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Shift into Neutral or Park
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended shift into neutral or park can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when the vehicle is in motion. This can lead to rear-end collisions, intersection accidents, or other safety hazards.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into neutral or park without warning
often at low speeds or when stopped at a traffic light
resulting in loss of power and unexpected stops. The driver may experience a sudden jolt
and the vehicle may not respond to accelerator input.
